headline: What Yum! Brands (YUM)'s Digital Push, Dividend Hike and Pizza Hut Review Mean For Shareholders
summary: Yum! Brands recently filed its 2025 Form 10-K, detailing past-year operations, expanded digital capabilities via its Byte by Yum! platform, a 6% increase in its quarterly dividend, share repurchases under a US$2.00 billion authorization, and acquisitions including 128 Taco Bell restaurants, alongside plans for a 2026 strategic review of Pizza Hut. headline: 1 S&P 500 Stock for Long-Term Investors and 2 We Turn Down
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is often seen as a benchmark for strong businesses, but that doesn’t mean every stock is worth owning. Some companies face significant challenges, whether it’s stagnating growth, heavy debt, or disruptive new competitors.
